    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If an animation is _always_ ticked unconditionally before rendering, a better fix would be to start the animations _before_ the first frame so that the tick brings them to the first frame.\n\nI believe the would entail setting `frame` initially to `CurrentSequence.Length - 1` as needed inside `Animation.cs`.\n\nYou would have to ensure Tick is always called before trying to render though, or the last frame would be displayed before looping around again.\n"
  },
